Delays due to track equipment repairs at Central earlier.

Some trains may be cancelled, terminate and commence from different locations or have a changed stopping pattern than timetabled.

Allow extra travel time, listen to announcements and check Station information screens before boarding trains.

AFL: Sydney Swans v Hawthorn Hawks - Sydney Cricket Ground, Moore Park
19:50 to 22:30
- The closest stations to the SCG is Central. From Central, light rail services and shuttle buses will run frequently to Moore Park leaving from Chalmers Street.
- You can also walk between Central and Moore Park via Devonshire St and the Albert 'Tibby' Cotter Walkway to avoid the queues.

NRL: Sharks v Panthers - Netstrata Jubilee Stadium, Kogarah
19:50 to 22:00
- The closest station to Netstrata Jubilee Stadium is Carlton on the T4 Eastern Suburbs & Illawarra Line. The stadium is a 10 minute walk from the station via Jubilee Avenue.

NRL: Sea Eagles v Cowboys - Brookvale Oval, Brookvale
18:00 to 20:00
- The best stations for connections to Brookvale Oval are Chatswood, North Sydney and Wynyard, from there change for a bus service running towards Warringah Mall or Brookvale.

For details, please visit https://transportnsw.info/events/2021/06

Station Update - Canterbury, Dulwich Hill, Hurlstone Park and more
Due to Metro construction works, platforms have a reduced capacity. Please avoid standing in front of the construction zones and remain behind the yellow line on the platforms.
Station Update - Bexley North, Birrong, Redfern
Due to station redevelopment work some platforms have reduced capacity. Please avoid standing in front of construction zones and remain behind the yellow line on the platform

Ongoing until 30 June some stairs between the station and the street level will close for upgrade works. During this time follow the signs and staff directions to the nearest available stairs. If you need further assistance, see station staff or call 93794110.

The stairs from Richardsons Crescent to concourse are closed for maintenance work until November 2021. Access to platforms 2 and 3 is via platform 1 side entrance (off carpark on Richardsons Crescent). Entrance from Griffiths St is not affected.
The escalator at the City end of platform 1 & 2 is closed for maintenance. Please follow signs and staff directions to the nearest escalators or lift to get on and off the platform.

There are changes happening at Central Station due to Sydney Metro construction works. Access to certain areas of the station and platforms may mean using different stairs, escalators and lifts. Please follow the signs and staff directions. If you need assistance, see station staff. For detailed information please visit https://transportnsw.info/alerts/details#/6062419

Changed traffic conditions may impact how you make your way to and from the station. There is a new pedestrian crossing at the corner of Bourke St and Church Ave. Bus stops, loading zones and taxi zones have been relocated while the parking lanes and the cycle lane have been closed.
Commuter parking has been reduced at St Marys Station. For more information please see signage around the station or visit www.transport.nsw.gov.au/stmarys

A new Metro concourse is being constructed on the northern end of Sydenham Station. 
While the concourse is being installed, please use the first 5 carriages of the train on platforms 4 & 6 and the last 6 carriages of the train on platform 5. 
If you need help, please ask staff at the station. For more information on these upgrades, please see sydneymetro.info

Until November 2021, the escalators to Exit 1 (Wynyard Park) will undergo upgrade works. Please follow the signs and staff directions to the nearest available stairs or lift. If you need assistance, see station staff or call 9224 2959.
